			<p>Your privacy is our primary concern. At Leema, we work hard to earn and keep your trust, so we adhere to the following principles to protect your privacy:</p>

			<ul>
				<li>We do not rent or sell your personally identifiable information to third parties for marketing purposes.</li>
				<li>We will not share your contact information with another User without your consent.</li>
				<li>We secure any personally identifiable information that you provide with industry standard protocols and technology.</li>
				<li>We reserve the right to modify this privacy statement at any time, so please review it frequently. If we make any material changes to this policy, we will notify you here or by means of a notice on our home page. By continuing to use the Leema service after notice of changes have been sent to you or published on the Leema website, you are consenting to the changes.</li>
			</ul>

			<p>Some important information in this Privacy Policy includes:</p>

			<ul>
				<li>The personally identifiable information of yours that is collected by Leema.</li>
				<li>How the information is used.</li>
				<li>With whom the information may be shared.</li>
				<li>How you can access and change your Account settings.</li>
				<li>What security procedures are in place to protect the loss, misuse or alteration of information collected by Leema.</li>
				<li>How to contact us.</li>
			</ul>

			<h5>Personal Information Collected:</h5>
			<p>The Leema site permits Users to voluntarily provide information about themselves for the purposes of offering, selling or purchasing goods in an online marketplace. By becoming a User, you willingly provide us certain personal information, which we collect in order to allow you to benefit from the Leema website. If you have any hesitation about providing such information to us and/or having such information displayed on the Leema website or otherwise used in any manner permitted in this Privacy Policy and the Terms of Use, you should not become a member of the Leema community.</p>

			<p>We collect your personal information in the following ways:</p>

			<ol>
				<li>
					<div id="registration">
						<h5>Registration</h5>
						<p>
							In order to become a User, you must first create an account on our website. To create an account, you are required to provide the following contact information, which you recognize and expressly acknowledge is personal information that allows others, including Leema, to identify you:
						</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Name</li>
							<li>E-mail Address</li>
							<li>Username and Password chosen by you</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</li>
				<li>
					<div id="profile-information">
						<h5>Profile Information</h5>
						<p>
							Buyer<br>
							Once you become a Buyer, you may provide additional information in your Profile section including your city, state, profile photograph, and a brief description about yourself.<br><br>

							Seller<br>
							To become a Seller, you first must register as a Buyer and, additionally, you must provide your full address (city, state, ZIP, country), telephone contact information, and bank account information (Note: Leema does not store any banking information - see Section X for further details).<br><br>

							Storefront<br>
							A Seller may provide additional information in his or her Storefront regarding the product(s), terms of sale, store policies, and any additional information you choose to include that complies with Leema’s <a href="/terms-of-use">Terms of Use</a>.
						</p>
						<p>Providing additional information beyond what is required at registration or to become a Buyer or Seller is entirely optional. Any information you provide at registration, in your Seller Profile, or in your Storefront that is not personally identifiable may be used in the same manner and extent to which other information that is not personally identifiable is permitted to be used hereunder. If you choose not to complete your profile you may lose the potential benefit of being a User. Leema reserves the right to remove any profiles that remain incomplete.</p>
					</div>
				</li>
				<li>
					<div id="customer-service">
						<h5>Customer Service</h5>
						<p>Leema may collect information through the Leema website or through customer service emails in order to, among other things, accurately categorize and respond to a customer’s inquiry and deliver appropriate service levels.</p>
					</div>
				</li>
				<li>
					<div id="cookies">
						<h5>Cookies</h5>
						<p>Leema uses cookies and web log files to track site usage. A cookie is a small data file which resides on your computer which allows Leema to recognize you as a User when you return to the Leema website using the same computer and web browser. Like the information you enter at registration or in your Storefront, cookie and log file data is used to customize your experience on our website.</p>

						<p>One type of cookie, known as a "persistent" cookie, is set once you’ve logged in to your Leema account. The next time you visit the Leema website, the persistent cookie will allow us to recognize you as an existing User so you will not need to log in before using the service. In order to access or change any of your private information (like a credit card number) or to send a message to another User, however, you must log in securely again with your password even if your computer contains your persistent cookie.</p>

						<p>Additionally, if you log out of the Leema website you will need to re-enter your password the next time you visit in order to log in to your account. Another type of cookie, called a "session" cookie, is used to identify a particular visit to the Leema website. Session cookies expire after a short time or when you close your web browser.</p>

						<p>We use cookies to improve the quality of our service by storing User preferences and tracking User trends. In the course of optimizing services for our Users, we may allow authorized third parties to place or recognize a unique cookie on your browser. Any information provided to third parties through such cookies will not be personally identifiable but may provide general segment information, e.g. your industry or geographic location, etc… Most browsers are initially set up to accept cookies, but you can reset your browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. Unfortunately, if your browser settings do not allow cookies or you opt to refuse all cookies, you may not be able to use the Leema website or services. Leema does not store personally identifiable information in the cookies.</p>
					</div>
				</li>
				<li>
					<div id="tracking">
						<h5>Tracking</h5>
						<p>Leema uses Google Analytics to gather information on User experience to better improve the functionality of the site.  Information gathered includes, but is not limited to: the URL of the site from which you came and the site to which you are going when you leave Leema, the Internet protocol (IP) address of your computer (or the proxy server you use to access the World Wide Web), your computer operating system and type of web browser you are using, as well as the name of your ISP. This information is used to analyze overall trends to help us improve the Leema service. The linkage between your IP address and your personally identifiable information is not shared with third-parties without your permission except when required by law.</p>
					</div>
				</li>
			</ol>

